b'' b'here is the latest on relocating your help files to a server.' b'the winhelp() function, as i am told by ms, does search your path so' b"relocating ms windows helpfiles won't be a problem as long as you include" b'the path to where you move them to, however, if an application has' b'hardcoded the path into their code so that when winhelp is invoked it' b'searches the given path (i.e. winhelp(hwnd, c:\\amipro) for example) then' b'winhelp does not search your path and instead looks only to that directory' b'where you have installed your software.' b'' b'i tested this out on a variety of software packages. i moved all my' b'helpfiles to the drive z:\\ and included this in the path statement.' b'here is the results for different software packages:' b'' b'' b'norton desktop\t\t\tfound helpfiles' b'windows v3.1 for workgroups\tfound helpfiles' b'windows v3.1\t\t\tfound helpfiles' b'ms powerpoint v3.0\t\tfound helpfiles' b'ms word\t\t\t\tfound helpfiles' b'ms excel v4.0a\t\t\tdid not find helpfiles (strange)' b'ms foxpro v2.5 for windows\tfound helpfiles' b'lotus amipro v3.0\t\tdid not find helpfiles' b'procomm plus for windows\tdid not find helpfiles' b'' b'' b'i guess this is better than nothing but it would make sense to be able to' b'specify a global path for helpfiles.' b'' b'if anyone has any comments or if i can help anyone or if i left something' b'out please let me know.' b'' b'' b'' b'more info on this topic as it develops' b'' 